        {
            "title": "How the Delayed US Inflation Report May Change Fed Day",
            "description": "<div class=\"txt-s4 article-text\"><div class=\"akcelo-wrapper akcelo-video media--169\" style=\"width:100%\"><div class=\"border:solid 1px #C0C0C0\" id=\"Zonebourse_Article_Video\" video-id=\"k5jIno9sRNMLQ0E4MNs\"><div itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"https://schema.org/VideoObject\"><meta content=\"How the Delayed US Inflation Report May Change Fed Day\" itemprop=\"name\"/><meta content=\"The US Labor Department has called furloughed employees back to work to put together the Consumer Price Index report. Bloomberg TV's Mike McKee explains what September's numbers could show, and how the Fed might react.\n\" itemprop=\"description\"/><meta content=\"2025-10-23T22:23:41+02:00\" itemprop=\"uploadDate\"/><meta content=\"/images/mtnewswires/A3483602.png\" itemprop=\"thumbnailUrl\"/><meta content=\"https://geo.dailymotion.com/player/x80uo.html?video=k5jIno9sRNMLQ0E4MNs\" itemprop=\"embedUrl\"/></div></div></div>\n               The US Labor Department has called furloughed employees back to work to put together the Consumer Price Index report. Bloomberg TV's Mike McKee explains what September's numbers could show, and how the Fed might react.<p><span class=\"js-l-obf link link--blue\" data-lobf=\"v4fox4ar=NTQyQxJmBMKwpP7nl8C=BbKwgTpvkfAwLuu\" data-tobf=\"blank\" onclick=\"gaEvent('Out', 'mtnewswires', '51428312');\">Bloomberg videos</span>, provided by MT Newswires</p></div>",
            "link": "https://hk.marketscreener.com/news/how-the-delayed-us-inflation-report-may-change-fed-day-ce7d5dd8d18af626",
            "pub_date": "2025-10-24 04:25:33",
            "source": "marketscreener",
            "kind": 1,
            "language": "en"
        },
        {
            "title": "ConocoPhillips to layoff Canada employees in November, company memo shows",
            "description": "<div class=\"txt-s4 article-text\"><p>HOUSTON (Reuters) -U.S. oil producer ConocoPhillips will begin layoffs at its Canadian operations in the first week of November, according to a memo seen by Reuters on Thursday. </p><p>\n              Employees in Calgary will be notified on November 5 virtually, and those in Surmont and Montney will be told in person on the following day, three sources told Reuters, citing the memo. </p><!-- Article --><p>\n              ConocoPhillips employs 950 people in Canada, according to the company's website. </p><p>\n              \"We will not be sharing area-specific workforce numbers for current or impacted employees and contractors,\" ConocoPhillips spokesperson Dennis Nuss said in an email. </p><p></p><p> (Reporting by Georgina McCartney and Arathy Somasekhar in Houston, Amanda Stephenson in Calgary, Editing by Franklin Paul)</p></div>",
            "link": "https://hk.marketscreener.com/news/conocophillips-to-layoff-canada-employees-in-november-company-memo-shows-ce7d5dd8d18bfe24",
            "pub_date": "2025-10-24 04:25:34",
            "source": "marketscreener",
            "kind": 1,
            "language": "en"
